{
  "text": "Indeed, Balakrishnan & Dogra explain how, under condition (2), a function can be constructed that cuts out X(Q \u2113 ) 2 explicitly (following [CITATION_1] this method is termed Quadratic Chabauty). They then apply this method to determine the rational points on several genus 2 curves that have the form",
